# {{.Name}}

Catuaba app — Go + Gin + GORM + Templ + HTMX + Tailwind CSS.

## Commands

```bash
make dev          # Start dev server (templ + tailwind + wgo hot-reload)
make build        # Production build
make test         # Run all tests
make tidy         # go mod tidy
```

## MCP Server

This project has an MCP server. **Always prefer MCP resources/tools over reading files directly** — they return compact JSON and save tokens.

### Setup

Add to your MCP config (`claude_desktop_config.json` or `.mcp.json`):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "catuaba": {
      "command": "catuaba",
      "args": ["mcp"]
    }
  }
}
```

### Resources (read-only, use FIRST to understand the project)

| URI | Returns | Use instead of |
|-----|---------|----------------|
| `catuaba://project/overview` | Module name, Go version, DB driver, port, plugins, directories | Reading go.mod, .env, listing dirs |
| `catuaba://project/models` | All model structs with fields, types, tags | Reading app/models/*.go |
| `catuaba://project/routes` | All HTTP routes: method, path, handler | Reading config/routes.go |
| `catuaba://project/controllers` | All controller packages and exported functions | Reading app/controllers/**/*.go |
| `catuaba://project/middleware` | All middleware functions with file locations | Reading middleware/*.go |
| `catuaba://project/env` | Environment variable names (no values) | Reading .env |

### Tools (actions — use to generate code)

| Tool | Args | What it does |
|------|------|-------------|
| `generate_scaffold` | `name`, `fields` (comma-separated, e.g. `"title:string,body:text"`) | Creates model + SQL migration + HTML handlers + Templ views + view routes + API controllers + API routes |
| `generate_model` | `name`, `fields` | Creates model + SQL migration |
| `get_model` | `name` (optional) | Returns model struct details (all if name omitted) |
| `get_routes` | `prefix` (optional) | Returns routes (filter by prefix like `/api/` or `/posts`) |
| `get_logs` | `lines`, `level`, `path` (all optional) | Recent app logs, filtered |
| `run_command` | `command`, `args` | Run any catuaba generate subcommand |
| `install_plugin` | `source` | Install a Catuaba plugin |

### Workflow: use MCP first, read files only when needed

1. **Read `catuaba://project/overview`** to understand the project
2. **Read `catuaba://project/models`** and **`catuaba://project/routes`** to see what exists
3. **Use `generate_scaffold`** or **`generate_model`** to create resources — do NOT write model/handler/route code manually
4. Only read individual files when you need to modify existing logic

## Project Structure

```
application.go              # Entrypoint: middleware stack, static files, routes, graceful shutdown
config/
  config.go                 # Env vars → AppConfig struct
  routes.go                 # SetupRoutes() — auto-injected by generators
database/
  connection.go             # GORM connection + SQL migration runner
  migrations/               # SQL files: {timestamp}_create_{table}.{up,down}.sql
app/
  models/                   # GORM models with gorm.Model (ID, CreatedAt, UpdatedAt, DeletedAt)
  controllers/
    home.go                 # Home page handler
    {resource}/             # HTML scaffold handlers (index, show, new, create, edit, update, delete)
    api/{resource}/         # JSON API handlers (index, show, create, update, delete)
  views/
    layouts/base.templ      # HTML5 layout: head, nav, flash, footer
    components/             # nav, flash, pagination, form_field
    pages/                  # home, not_found
    {resource}/             # index, show, form (scaffold-generated)
middleware/                 # health, logger, cors, recovery, request_id, session, csrf, flash, rate_limit, secure_headers{{if .Auth}}
  require_auth.go           # Auth middleware — checks session for userID{{end}}
static/
  css/input.css             # Tailwind source (@import "tailwindcss")
  css/app.css               # Compiled (gitignored, generated by Tailwind CLI)
```

## Architecture Patterns

### Models

```go
// app/models/post.go
type Post struct {
    gorm.Model                    // ID uint, CreatedAt, UpdatedAt, DeletedAt
    Title   string `json:"title"`
    Body    string `json:"body"`
}
```

- Always embed `gorm.Model`
- JSON tags use snake_case
- Migrations are raw SQL in `database/migrations/` (not GORM AutoMigrate)

### HTML Handlers (scaffold)

Location: `app/controllers/{resource_plural}/`

Each handler is a separate file. Pattern:

```go
package posts

func Index(ctx *gin.Context) {
    // 1. Query with pagination
    // 2. Get flash messages: msg, typ := middleware.GetFlash(ctx)
    // 3. Set Content-Type header
    // 4. Render templ component: views.Index(items, page, totalPages, msg, typ).Render(ctx.Request.Context(), ctx.Writer)
}

func Create(ctx *gin.Context) {
    // 1. Bind form params with ctx.ShouldBind
    // 2. Validate → re-render form with errors on failure
    // 3. database.DB.Create(&item)
    // 4. middleware.SetFlash(ctx, "success", "Post created!")
    // 5. ctx.Redirect(http.StatusSeeOther, "/posts")
}
```

### API Controllers

Location: `app/controllers/api/{resource_plural}/`

Same pattern but returns JSON:
```go
ctx.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{"data": items})
```

### Views (Templ)

- `.templ` files compile to `_templ.go` (gitignored)
- Every page wraps in `@layouts.Base(title, appName, flashMsg, flashType) { ... }`
- Use `@components.Flash()`, `@components.Pagination()`, `@components.FormField()`
- HTMX: `hx-get`, `hx-post`, `hx-target`, `hx-push-url` for SPA-like navigation
- Alpine.js: `x-data`, `x-show`, `x-init` for client-side interactivity (flash dismiss, etc.)
- CSRF token auto-sent via HTMX (script in base layout reads `_csrf_token` cookie)

### Routes

`config/routes.go` is auto-managed by generators. Pattern:

```go
// HTML routes (scaffold):     GET/POST /resource, /resource/:id, /resource/:id/edit, etc.
// API routes:                  GET/POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE /api/resource, /api/resource/:id
```

HTML forms use POST for create/update/delete (no PUT/DELETE since browsers don't support it).

### Flash Messages

```go
middleware.SetFlash(ctx, "success", "Item saved!")  // Set before redirect
msg, typ := middleware.GetFlash(ctx)                 // Read in handler, pass to view
```

Types: `"success"`, `"error"`, `"warning"`
{{if .Auth}}
### Authentication

- Sessions via SCS (`middleware.SessionManager`)
- `middleware.SetSessionUser(ctx, userID, userName)` — login
- `middleware.ClearSession(ctx)` — logout
- `middleware.GetSessionUserID(ctx)` / `middleware.GetSessionUserName(ctx)` — check auth
- `middleware.RequireAuth()` — middleware that redirects to `/login`
- Passwords hashed with bcrypt (`golang.org/x/crypto/bcrypt`)
{{end}}
### CSRF Protection

- Auto-applied to POST/PUT/DELETE (skips `/api/` routes)
- Forms: include `<input type="hidden" name="_csrf_token" value={middleware.CSRFToken(ctx)}/>`
- HTMX: auto-handled by script in base layout (reads cookie, sends `X-CSRF-Token` header)

## Code Generation Quick Reference

```bash
# Full scaffold (model + migration + HTML handlers + views + API + routes)
catuaba g scaffold Post title:string body:text published:boolean

# API only (model + migration + JSON controllers + routes)
catuaba g api Product name:string price:float

# Model only (model + migration)
catuaba g model Category name:string

# Other generators
catuaba g controller Auth login logout register
catuaba g middleware RateLimit
catuaba g service EmailSender
catuaba g seed Posts
catuaba g migration add_category_id_to_posts
catuaba g view about
```

### Field types

| Type | Go type | SQL type | HTML input |
|------|---------|----------|------------|
| `string` | `string` | `VARCHAR(255)` | `text` |
| `text` | `string` | `TEXT` | `textarea` |
| `integer` | `int` | `INTEGER` | `number` |
| `float` | `float64` | `REAL` | `number` |
| `boolean` | `bool` | `BOOLEAN` | `checkbox` |
| `datetime` | `time.Time` | `TIMESTAMP` | `datetime-local` |

## Do NOT manually edit

- `config/routes.go` — auto-managed by generators (imports + route blocks injected via AST)
- `*_templ.go` files — generated by `templ generate`
- `static/css/app.css` — generated by Tailwind CLI
